 population at\n$P{\\sim}5000\\,$d. This shift cannot be reconciled by orbital evolution due to\nmass loss or mass transfer. At long periods, the evolutionary sequence\nO($\\xrightarrow{}$LBV)$\\xrightarrow{}$WN$\\xrightarrow{}$WC seems feasible. The\nhigh frequency of short-period WN binaries compared to WC binaries suggests\nthat they either tend to merge or that the WN components in these binaries\nrarely evolve into WC stars in the Galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Dec 2022 22:48:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-06-07"}
